 race and racism in recent decades and identifies the challenges and opportunities for policy and politically-engaged scholarship in future, clearly mapping the pitfalls and possibilities for critical work on race and racism. .  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRace awarenesszGreat Britain. 0aRace relationsxGovernment policyzGreat Britain. 0aRacismzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831111966330 cprintz978144731958040uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447319597?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447319597423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447319597/original  a978-3-11-119663-3  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles